snippet.title: CNET TV Bloopers 2013
snippet.description: It's the cream of the 2013 blooper crop, featuring some of your favorite CNET TV faces.

snippet.title: Always On Season 5 bloopers!
snippet.description: It's been an incredible run for all of us at Always On. This week's show features fun moments that happened in front of and behind the camera, including our entire team. Plus, a special clap montage.

snippet.title: Always On Season 4 bloopers!
snippet.description: It's the behind the scenes clips where Molly Wood and Jeff Cannata flub, move and groove, sing, and make us laugh. Oh yeah!

snippet.title: All the best CNET TV bloopers from Mobile World Congress
snippet.description: Not every CNET TV video goes off without a hitch. Yes, sometimes we stumble here and there. Check out the best bloopers from our Mobile World Congress team.

snippet.title: Always On: Season 3 Bloopers
snippet.description: Behind all the flashy gadgets, torture tests, and ideas of the future, the Always On crew suffers a nasty case of the bloopers.

snippet.title: Season 3 Bloopers!
snippet.description: We have to admit, we totally crack ourselves up! Check out the behind-the-scenes with an unboxing tongue twister, GoPro action setup shots never seen before, and a four-letter word that brings Molly to tears!

snippet.title: Always On: Bloopers and outtakes
snippet.description: Get an inside look at the bug bites, the surfing wipe-outs, and the sweaty DIY projects that amused and annoyed us all year long.

snippet.title: Season 4 bloopers: Singing, dancing, and a fire hose
snippet.description: It's our end-of-season bloopers show, our favorite and yours! Check out the flubs, the little dances, the brand-new drinking games, and our jumping skills.

snippet.title: Chrome for Android gets much-sought built-in translation
snippet.description: On-the-fly translation of Web pages is a fixture in Chrome for PCs, but now it's in the Android version, too. Also arriving: SPDY-augmented data compression.

snippet.title: Maj! Bing adds Klingon language translation
snippet.description: Go galactic with the newest addition to Bing Translator, an automated Klingon translation service that has you covered whether you're translating tribbles (yIHmey) or "Star Trek" (Hov trek).
